We also recommend Saipan.

18
00:00:22.420 --> 00:00:24.920
Gonda-kun, they haven't canceled, have they?

19
00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:25.660
Have they?!

20
00:00:25.660 --> 00:00:26.830
It'll be fine, Shinshi-san.

21
00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:28.730
Good morning, Kurokawa-san.

22
00:00:28.730 --> 00:00:29.560
Good morning.

23
00:00:29.560 --> 00:00:31.630
How many seats are left in the QR CMN?

24
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:32.930
The group canceled?!

25
00:00:31.630 --> 00:00:32.930
Eight.

26
00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:35.280
It's quiet in here.

27
00:00:36.230 --> 00:00:37.610
Hey, Ohara.

28
00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:39.980
Ohara!

29
00:00:40.390 --> 00:00:41.800
Y-Yes, ma'am?

30
00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:45.460
Confirm hotel reservations 
for this summer tour package.

31
00:00:46.420 --> 00:00:48.570
W-Will do, Branch Manager.

32
00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:51.000
Respond right away, and make eye contact!

33
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:52.160
Y-Yes, ma'am!

34
00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:55.300
Stop zoning out. We're busy here.

35
00:00:55.300 --> 00:00:56.470
I swear...

36
00:00:57.980 --> 00:00:59.830
<i>I'm not zoning out.</i>

37
00:01:00.230 --> 00:01:03.220
<i>I was considering how to respond.</i>

38
00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:05.530
<i>If you waited another second...</i>

39
00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:10.550
Ohara, 
let's play baseball.

40
00:01:06.820 --> 00:01:10.630
<i>Maybe it's my habit of lagging 
slightly behind in conversation,</i>

41
00:01:07.300 --> 00:01:10.550
Did you buy
 the new game?

42
00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:10.550
Did you do 
your homework?

43
00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:10.550
Why aren't you 
saying anything?

44
00:01:10.630 --> 00:01:13.730
<i>but it feels like I'm also 
falling behind in life.</i>

45
00:01:13.730 --> 00:01:15.350
Ohara-san.

46
00:01:15.630 --> 00:01:17.180
Good morning.

47
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:19.640
I'll leave these Hawaii 
yachting documents here for you.

48
00:01:22.310 --> 00:01:23.580
Thanks a bunch.

49
00:01:22.310 --> 00:01:24.770
<i>I missed my chance to say thanks again.</i>

50
00:01:23.580 --> 00:01:24.770
No problem.

51
00:01:25.490 --> 00:01:27.650
<i>Not that it was worth taking up her time.</i>

52
00:01:34.070 --> 00:01:35.700
<i>Honjoji-san?!</i>

53
00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:39.750
Hello, this is Ohara with JTC.

54
00:01:37.410 --> 00:01:40.100
<i>I'm working diligently! I'm not slacking!</i>

55
00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:42.940
About the Hawaii yachting. Right.

56
00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:50.710
Why Don't We Get Married?

57
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.960
Hikifune Station West Entrance

58
00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:56.590
Kama, I'm home.

59
00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:04.780
Here's your food.

60
00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:19.870
Kama, Honjoji-san glared at me again today.

61
00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:25.810
She's only been there a year longer than me, 
but she gives me those silent menacing looks.

62
00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:31.090
Kama-kun, I'm already 
in my fourth year of work.

63
00:02:31.090 --> 00:02:34.840
When are coworkers going to 
stop getting mad at me?

64
00:02:36.460 --> 00:02:39.100
Not that asking a cat is going to help.

65
00:02:41.350 --> 00:02:42.220
Walking the World's Streets

66
00:02:43.670 --> 00:02:47.360
Kama, come watch TV with me.

67
00:02:49.320 --> 00:02:53.060
Spending time with you like this is so nice.

68
00:02:54.540 --> 00:02:57.360
A travel agency starts its day with cleaning!

69
00:02:58.210 --> 00:02:59.960
Komiya-chan, you're so peppy.

70
00:02:59.960 --> 00:03:02.010
Okay, get to mopping.

71
00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:03.020
Thanks.

72
00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:10.790
<i>I'm not slacking! I'm not!</i>

73
00:03:10.790 --> 00:03:12.300
<i>I </i>am<i> cleaning!</i>

74
00:03:15.310 --> 00:03:17.510
<i>Did I scare him again?</i>

75
00:03:18.060 --> 00:03:21.010
<i>I suppose he thinks 
I'm a frightening person.</i>

76
00:03:21.390 --> 00:03:24.520
<i>I have this thing where 
I unconsciously stare at people.</i>

77
00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:27.270
<i>It's not like I'm doing it on purpose,</i>

78
00:03:27.670 --> 00:03:29.980
<i>but I can't think of anything to say.</i>

79
00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:32.160
I'm sorry, Honjoji-san!

80
00:03:32.160 --> 00:03:34.440
Did I do something bad?

81
00:03:35.310 --> 00:03:38.340
<i>No, I mean, I'm not angry.</i>

82
00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:40.450
<i>But I'm not smiling either.</i>

83
00:03:40.820 --> 00:03:44.950
<i>Oh well, it's not worth 
taking the time to explain.</i>

84
00:03:45.450 --> 00:03:46.960
This is Honjo-azumabashi

85
00:03:49.670 --> 00:03:52.920
Atlases

86
00:03:52.920 --> 00:03:54.800
Latest World Atlas

87
00:04:08.330 --> 00:04:10.810
Alone at last!

88
00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:15.030
Mercator of Love

89
00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:16.990
Mount Kaimon

90
00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:16.990
Kyushu Nature Trail

91
00:04:19.740 --> 00:04:23.330
<i>I thought that I could just look at maps
 all day in the Planning Department,</i>

92
00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:25.830
<i>but that's not how it turned out at all.</i>

93
00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:31.420
<i>So much fun for ¥435!</i>

94
00:04:31.420 --> 00:04:34.090
<i>Maps are the best!</i>

95
00:04:34.170 --> 00:04:35.840
JTC Tourist
 JTC Travel

96
00:04:34.170 --> 00:04:35.840
Go to Hawaii!!

97
00:04:34.610 --> 00:04:37.440
We will now begin today's morning assembly.

98
00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:41.810
First off, Mamaru-san from the head office 
has something important to say.

99
00:04:41.810 --> 00:04:43.100
<i>Someone from the head office?</i>

100
00:04:43.100 --> 00:04:46.230
Everyone, thank you for your hard work.

101
00:04:46.230 --> 00:04:49.060
We find ourselves now in the Reiwa era,

102
00:04:49.060 --> 00:04:52.820
and competition continues to heat up.

103
00:04:52.820 --> 00:04:55.570
So as for our company, uh...

104
00:04:55.570 --> 00:04:58.140
As of this summer, JTC will 
up its focus on North America.

105
00:04:58.140 --> 00:05:00.650
The Alaska area in particular.

106
00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:05.910
Alaska touches the Arctic, and its cities 
such as Juneau and Fairbanks are popular.

107
00:05:05.910 --> 00:05:08.780
And so, someone from this office 
is going to become manager

108
00:05:08.780 --> 00:05:11.920
of the Anchorage Branch 
that's going to open next year!

109
00:05:11.920 --> 00:05:13.790
<i>S-Say what?!</i>

110
00:05:13.790 --> 00:05:15.100
Anchorage?

111
00:05:15.100 --> 00:05:16.960
We're getting sent to Alaska?

112
00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:19.500
Oh, but it's a pretty place.

113
00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:21.790
It has icebergs, glaciers, dog sleds...

114
00:05:21.680 --> 00:05:22.890
North Pole

115
00:05:21.790 --> 00:05:23.340
That's the North Pole!

116
00:05:23.340 --> 00:05:25.990
It's a little far to be 
separated from family,

117
00:05:25.990 --> 00:05:29.150
so we'll select someone who's unmarried.

118
00:05:29.150 --> 00:05:31.310
Would anyone like to volunteer?!

119
00:05:31.310 --> 00:05:32.660
Unmarried?

120
00:05:32.660 --> 00:05:34.410
Then I'm off the hook.

121
00:05:34.410 --> 00:05:35.680
How about you, Saito?

122
00:05:35.680 --> 00:05:36.800
Oh, no.

123
00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:38.610
There aren't any volunteers?

124
00:05:38.610 --> 00:05:39.940
Excuse me.

125
00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:42.030
Ohara, are you going?

126
00:05:40.790 --> 00:05:43.350
I-I... can't go.

127
00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:45.840
Huh? Ohara?

128
00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:48.590
I-I, well...

129
00:05:48.590 --> 00:05:50.540
I have a cat.

130
00:05:52.540 --> 00:05:56.040
A cat? That's not a reason.

131
00:05:56.310 --> 00:05:58.140
You barely ever speak up,

132
00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:01.420
and now you make me wonder 
how you even view your job.

133
00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:04.390
Everyone give this some serious thought!

134
00:06:04.390 --> 00:06:06.590
365 days until the 
Anchorage Branch opens

135
00:06:04.390 --> 00:06:06.890
Because one of you is going!

136
00:06:09.910 --> 00:06:12.610
Alaska? What a surprise!

137
00:06:12.610 --> 00:06:16.380
Traveling there might be great, 
but living there's another matter.

138
00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:18.370
It's three or four years at the least.

139
00:06:18.370 --> 00:06:23.280
Kamoi-san has been stuck in Tahiti for ten 
years now, with no replacement in sight.

140
00:06:20.150 --> 00:06:23.280
Please send me home.

141
00:06:20.150 --> 00:06:23.280
Please send me home. Please send me home!

142
00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:24.410
Hey!

143
00:06:24.410 --> 00:06:28.170
I know how to guard against going to Alaska!

144
00:06:28.170 --> 00:06:29.120
Seriously?

145
00:06:29.460 --> 00:06:32.230
Just get married!

146
00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:35.330
They prefer someone who's single, after all.

147
00:06:35.330 --> 00:06:38.800
Good idea. Komiya-chan, will you marry me?

148
00:06:38.800 --> 00:06:42.100
Oh, what a thing to say!

149
00:06:42.780 --> 00:06:46.750
<i>Never mind marriage, 
I don't even have any female friends.</i>

150
00:06:46.750 --> 00:06:49.470
<i>I'm in trouble. Lots of trouble.</i>

151
00:06:55.370 --> 00:06:59.770
<i>It's 5,500 km to Anchorage. That's too far.</i>

152
00:06:59.770 --> 00:07:04.110
<i>I don't even communicate well 
in Japan. Forget Alaska.</i>

153
00:07:04.110 --> 00:07:07.820
<i>And I hear the mosquitoes there are monsters.</i>

154
00:07:08.130 --> 00:07:09.630
<i>What do I do?</i>

155
00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:12.870
<i>This is a matter of life and death for me.</i>

156
00:07:15.460 --> 00:07:18.080
<i>And it's not like I have any pull at work.</i>

157
00:07:18.590 --> 00:07:21.750
<i>Everywhere in the world is fun on a map.</i>

158
00:07:21.750 --> 00:07:25.340
<i>But actually going out in public 
doesn't interest me at all.</i>

159
00:07:25.730 --> 00:07:28.500
<i>I bet it's cold in Alaska.</i>

160
00:07:32.810 --> 00:07:35.560
It was scary at the vet, huh, Kama?

161
00:07:35.560 --> 00:07:37.730
But for the time being, you're...

162
00:07:41.320 --> 00:07:43.270
Honjoji-san?

163
00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:49.170
<i>N-No, there's no need to be nervous.</i>

164
00:07:49.170 --> 00:07:51.530
<i>We're not at work today. If I slack off...</i>

165
00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:52.800
<i>it's okay.</i>

166
00:07:54.890 --> 00:07:57.170
Excuse me, Honjoji-san.

167
00:07:59.340 --> 00:08:01.670
Thank you for all your help.

168
00:08:03.320 --> 00:08:06.800
I'm leaving the company.

169
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:08.510
You quit?

170
00:08:08.510 --> 00:08:11.820
Oh, no, I plan to tell 
Kurokawa-san on Monday.

171
00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:13.720
S-See you.

172
00:08:15.110 --> 00:08:17.390
Um, is that...

173
00:08:17.390 --> 00:08:19.430
because your cat is important to you?

174
00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:21.560
Yes, it is.

175
00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:24.470
He's finally willing to show his tail to me.

176
00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:25.990
His tail?

177
00:08:25.990 --> 00:08:29.320
Other cats would pick on him.

178
00:08:29.320 --> 00:08:31.420
He was a mess when I got him.

179
00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.730
It took forever for him to open up to me.

180
00:08:35.200 --> 00:08:39.760
But lately, he's at least 
started showing his tail.

181
00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:44.460
I can't go and abandon him now.

182
00:08:44.460 --> 00:08:46.730
There's no one who can look after him?

183
00:08:46.730 --> 00:08:48.300
A girlfriend or family member?

184
00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:50.660
No, not at all! Uh, I...

185
00:08:52.470 --> 00:08:55.420
I'm sorry for always being unsociable.

186
00:08:55.870 --> 00:08:57.310
Bye.

187
00:08:59.980 --> 00:09:01.100
Um!

188
00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:03.860
Do you know what the summer 
temperature is in Anchorage?

189
00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:04.400
Huh?

190
00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:07.080
It's 18°C. A little chilly.

191
00:09:08.530 --> 00:09:12.190
What I'm trying to say is, well...

192
00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:14.480
Why don't...

193
00:09:14.990 --> 00:09:16.740
we get married?

194
00:09:26.660 --> 00:09:29.920
Why don't we get married?

195
00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:32.180
Huh?

196
00:09:32.180 --> 00:09:32.950
Huh?

197
00:09:33.520 --> 00:09:34.250
Huh?

198
00:09:34.250 --> 00:09:35.050
Huh?

199
00:09:35.050 --> 00:09:37.530
No, I'm asking you.

200
00:09:37.530 --> 00:09:39.180
Oh, right.

201
00:09:39.180 --> 00:09:41.550
<i>Did she just say "married"?</i>

202
00:09:41.550 --> 00:09:42.690
<i>Married?</i>

203
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:46.570
<i>He's surprised. And I admit, 
it was a wild thing to say.</i>

204
00:09:46.570 --> 00:09:47.460
Huh?

205
00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:48.540
Huh?

206
00:09:48.540 --> 00:09:52.170
U-Um, what do you mean by "married"?

207
00:09:52.170 --> 00:09:55.410
I don't mean a real marriage. Just pretend.

208
00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:56.280
Pretend?

209
00:09:56.280 --> 00:10:01.130
That's right. I could never 
handle the Anchorage Branch.

210
00:10:01.130 --> 00:10:04.420
But if I'm ordered to go, 
I have no grounds for refusal.

211
00:10:04.420 --> 00:10:06.660
It's the same for you, isn't it?

212
00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:09.000
If you can't be apart from your cat,

213
00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:15.220
we could get married and 
then not have to go to Alaska.

214
00:10:15.220 --> 00:10:19.430
Kurokawa-san was saying unmarried 
people will be prioritized.

215
00:10:20.070 --> 00:10:23.730
So if we were to make it so we're married...

216
00:10:23.730 --> 00:10:26.110
<i>I hadn't thought of that.</i>

217
00:10:26.110 --> 00:10:29.130
<i>No wait, I could never. A pretend marriage?</i>

218
00:10:29.130 --> 00:10:32.570
<i>I've hardly ever even spoken to Honjoji-san!</i>

219
00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:35.390
<i>Now I've gone and said it all.</i>

220
00:10:35.390 --> 00:10:37.570
<i>There's no backing out now.</i>

221
00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:42.130
Is a fake marriage really going to work?

222
00:10:42.130 --> 00:10:44.120
I'm confident it will.

223
00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:48.330
I shouldn't say this, but 
we don't stand out at work.

224
00:10:48.330 --> 00:10:52.630
If we say we're getting married, 
I doubt anyone will show much interest.

225
00:10:53.130 --> 00:10:54.840
365 days until the 
Anchorage Branch opens

226
00:10:53.130 --> 00:10:55.670
The Anchorage Branch opens in a year.

227
00:10:55.670 --> 00:10:58.310
If we say we're getting married 
and then make it through several months,

228
00:10:58.310 --> 00:11:00.200
there'll be no more talk about the transfer,

229
00:11:00.200 --> 00:11:04.890
and by then, hardly anyone should 
care anymore about our marriage.

230
00:11:05.240 --> 00:11:09.080
I think we'll be okay to let things die 
down, then pretend it never happened.

231
00:11:11.010 --> 00:11:12.940
You know, you have a point there.

232
00:11:12.940 --> 00:11:13.900
Right.

233
00:11:15.330 --> 00:11:17.930
<i>Is this actually a good idea?</i>

234
00:11:17.930 --> 00:11:22.660
<i>I want to keep my job, and 
I'll get to stay with Kama!</i>

235
00:11:23.760 --> 00:11:27.580
Well, I'm on board with trying it.

236
00:11:27.580 --> 00:11:28.920
The fake marriage.

237
00:11:28.920 --> 00:11:31.750
Thank you, let's give it a go.

238
00:11:32.540 --> 00:11:36.670
So, tomorrow at 8:45, let's meet 
at the street-side entrance.

239
00:11:36.670 --> 00:11:39.410
We'll notify Kurokawa-san 
of our marriage there.

240
00:11:39.410 --> 00:11:41.150
I'll move things forward from here,

241
00:11:41.150 --> 00:11:43.650
so Ohara-kun, you basically 
don't need to do anything.

242
00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:44.570
What?

243
00:11:44.570 --> 00:11:46.780
There's nothing for me to do?

244
00:11:46.780 --> 00:11:47.910
There is not.

245
00:11:47.910 --> 00:11:51.670
I proposed this idea, 
so you can leave it to me.

246
00:11:51.670 --> 00:11:52.650
If you'll excuse me.

247
00:11:55.070 --> 00:11:57.790
<i>Th-That was so businesslike.</i>

248
00:11:57.790 --> 00:12:02.200
<i>You know what, I had no idea 
Honjoji-san was such a bold person.</i>

249
00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:03.610
<i>It's surprising.</i>

250
00:12:03.610 --> 00:12:05.880
<i>It's now or never.</i>

251
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:08.210
What?!

252
00:12:08.510 --> 00:12:10.790
Married?! You two?!

253
00:12:10.790 --> 00:12:12.790
Y-Yes.

254
00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:17.140
<i>I need to tell her the way I planned.</i>

255
00:12:17.720 --> 00:12:20.530
The two of us would like 
to keep this quiet and low-key,

256
00:12:20.530 --> 00:12:23.390
so as not to cause any trouble.

257
00:12:23.390 --> 00:12:26.500
Wow! Congratulations!

258
00:12:26.500 --> 00:12:29.250
No way, I didn't notice at <i>all</i>!

259
00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:31.900
When did you start dating?!

260
00:12:31.900 --> 00:12:35.220
And Ohara! I never 
thought you had it in you!

261
00:12:35.220 --> 00:12:37.030
Way to prove me wrong!

262
00:12:35.630 --> 00:12:37.030
U-Um...

263
00:12:37.030 --> 00:12:39.060
What a great pair you make!

264
00:12:39.060 --> 00:12:41.090
What a great pair!

265
00:12:41.090 --> 00:12:42.740
You've made my day!

266
00:12:42.740 --> 00:12:44.750
Excuse me, Kurokawa-san.

267
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:48.300
Well, I'm sure there's a lot ahead of you,

268
00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:51.630
but I'm happy to offer any advice. See ya!

269
00:12:55.440 --> 00:12:57.780
She was unbelievably happy.

270
00:12:57.780 --> 00:12:58.510
Yes.

271
00:12:58.990 --> 00:13:01.050
So far, the plan's a success.

272
00:13:01.050 --> 00:13:01.730
Huh?

273
00:13:01.730 --> 00:13:04.020
She believes we're going to get married.

274
00:13:04.810 --> 00:13:09.150
You don't need to worry, 
I'll make sure this works.

275
00:13:14.100 --> 00:13:14.730
Hello.

276
00:13:14.730 --> 00:13:16.470
What?! Another accident?!

277
00:13:16.470 --> 00:13:18.610
They're going to cancel on us!

278
00:13:18.610 --> 00:13:20.920
Shinshi-san, calm down.

279
00:13:18.610 --> 00:13:21.610
Please hurry and update the site.

280
00:13:29.800 --> 00:13:30.870
Ohara, Ohara.

281
00:13:30.870 --> 00:13:32.250
Y-Yes, ma'am.

282
00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:35.500
We're having trouble filling 
these Hawaii hotel rooms.

283
00:13:35.500 --> 00:13:37.640
Could you quickly come up with a plan?

284
00:13:37.640 --> 00:13:38.380
Will do.

285
00:13:38.380 --> 00:13:40.790
I'd like you to help him, Honjoji-san.

286
00:13:40.790 --> 00:13:41.510
Yes, ma'am.

287
00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:43.280
Please do, then.

288
00:13:43.280 --> 00:13:44.800
Saito, you got a minute?

289
00:13:44.800 --> 00:13:46.020
Yes, ma'am.

290
00:13:46.020 --> 00:13:48.790
Listen, about what I asked you 
for the other day,

291
00:13:48.790 --> 00:13:49.660
how's it coming?

292
00:13:49.660 --> 00:13:50.560
It isn't finished yet.

293
00:13:52.810 --> 00:13:54.190
Five Hotel 
New Plan Summary

294
00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:54.190
Done.

295
00:13:54.190 --> 00:13:55.930
That took a long time.

296
00:13:55.930 --> 00:13:57.150
Yes.

297
00:13:57.150 --> 00:13:58.110
Hello?

298
00:13:58.110 --> 00:14:00.430
<i>It's done? Oh, good!</i>

299
00:14:00.430 --> 00:14:02.950
<i>Right now we're meeting up 
at the usual Italian place.</i>

300
00:14:02.950 --> 00:14:04.360
<i>Would you mind bringing it there?</i>

301
00:14:04.360 --> 00:14:06.860
<i>Make sure Honjoji-san comes with you.</i>

302
00:14:07.910 --> 00:14:09.700
The usual Italian place?

303
00:14:09.700 --> 00:14:12.880
Oh, that would be Bau Bau.

304
00:14:12.880 --> 00:14:13.830
Let's go.

305
00:14:13.830 --> 00:14:16.330
Ristorante Bau Bau

306
00:14:16.330 --> 00:14:17.840
Ohara-kun Honjoji-san
Congrats on getting engaged!!
All of us at the JTC Kinshicho Branch

307
00:14:17.830 --> 00:14:20.080
Ohara-kun Honjoji-san
Congrats on getting engaged!!
All of us at the JTC Kinshicho Branch

308
00:14:18.290 --> 00:14:20.920
Congratulations!

309
00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:23.840
<i>A surprise party?</i>

310
00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:25.450
Are you surprised?

311
00:14:25.450 --> 00:14:27.680
We all put it together!

312
00:14:27.680 --> 00:14:29.990
Come on, you two, sit in the middle.

313
00:14:29.990 --> 00:14:31.810
You're the stars today!

314
00:14:31.810 --> 00:14:33.950
<i>Th-This isn't good.</i>

315
00:14:33.950 --> 00:14:35.630
<i>What do we do now?</i>

316
00:14:35.630 --> 00:14:36.750
Ohara-kun.

317
00:14:37.600 --> 00:14:39.520
There's no escaping this.

318
00:14:39.520 --> 00:14:41.320
Let's just run with it.

319
00:14:41.320 --> 00:14:41.990
Huh?

320
00:14:41.990 --> 00:14:44.670
We can't afford to let them set the pace.

321
00:14:44.670 --> 00:14:48.370
Let's return fire at max excitement!

322
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:50.150
<i>Max excitement?</i>

323
00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:51.990
<i>Is that something we can do?</i>

324
00:14:53.080 --> 00:14:54.420
Don't worry.

325
00:14:54.420 --> 00:14:58.080
I take full responsibility for this. 
Just give me a little time.

326
00:14:58.080 --> 00:15:01.090
So, in celebration of their engagement!

327
00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:01.090
I'm going to go charge up my excitement.

328
00:15:01.090 --> 00:15:03.830
Cheers!

329
00:15:05.060 --> 00:15:07.050
<i>Charge up her excitement?</i>

330
00:15:07.380 --> 00:15:09.150
<i>Is that something she can do?!</i>

331
00:15:10.810 --> 00:15:14.890
Senpai, could you tell us the whole story?

332
00:15:14.890 --> 00:15:18.320
Tell us how you fell in love!

333
00:15:16.390 --> 00:15:18.320
Uh, well...

334
00:15:18.320 --> 00:15:19.540
You happy boy, you!

335
00:15:19.540 --> 00:15:20.770
Uh, well, see...

336
00:15:20.770 --> 00:15:22.010
Happy boy!

337
00:15:22.010 --> 00:15:28.270
Still, I can't help but be surprised that 
Ohara-san and Honjoji-san are an item.

338
00:15:28.270 --> 00:15:30.740
Komiya-chan, aren't you suspicious?

339
00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:31.620
Huh?

340
00:15:31.620 --> 00:15:34.340
It's too sudden, this engagement.

341
00:15:34.340 --> 00:15:36.620
The whole timing of it.

342
00:15:36.620 --> 00:15:38.480
It really is fishy.

343
00:15:39.580 --> 00:15:40.790
I bet...

344
00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:43.140
there's a bun in the oven!

345
00:15:44.380 --> 00:15:46.220
I'm impressed, Ohara-san!

346
00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:44.830
Noisy

347
00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:45.340
Noisy

348
00:15:45.420 --> 00:15:45.840
Noisy

349
00:15:45.920 --> 00:15:46.340
Noisy

350
00:15:46.220 --> 00:15:48.600
Yeah, I had no clue!

351
00:15:46.420 --> 00:15:46.750
Noisy

352
00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:50.770
Don't tell me it's a shotgun wedding?

353
00:15:52.330 --> 00:15:55.480
<i>Th-They're going to tear me apart.</i>

354
00:15:55.480 --> 00:15:58.100
<i>I've got to find a way to escape!</i>

355
00:15:56.260 --> 00:15:56.350
Noisy

356
00:15:56.430 --> 00:15:56.850
Noisy

357
00:15:56.930 --> 00:15:57.350
Noisy

358
00:15:56.930 --> 00:15:57.350
Noisy

359
00:15:57.430 --> 00:15:57.850
Noisy

360
00:15:57.930 --> 00:15:58.350
Noisy

361
00:15:58.430 --> 00:15:58.850
Noisy

362
00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:04.730
Program

363
00:16:07.580 --> 00:16:11.340
Everyone, thank you for being here today.

364
00:16:11.340 --> 00:16:13.990
As thanks, I'm going to sing!

365
00:16:13.990 --> 00:16:18.000
Mercator of Love

366
00:16:13.990 --> 00:16:18.000
Written by Narita Shun
 Music by Narita Shun
 Arrangement by Narita Shun

367
00:16:18.480 --> 00:16:22.880
My love is a Mercator...

368
00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:26.160
<i>Th-This is Honjoji-san at max excitement!</i>

369
00:16:28.030 --> 00:16:30.140
<i>Or, not so much.</i>

370
00:16:31.320 --> 00:16:35.020
<i>That singing that sounded like it was coming 
from Hades brought the place to a standstill.</i>

371
00:16:36.360 --> 00:16:40.210
<i>She had probably never sung 
in front of people before.</i>

372
00:16:40.770 --> 00:16:44.220
<i>But her only choice was to sing.</i>

373
00:16:44.850 --> 00:16:49.230
<i>To me, she seemed downright heroic.</i>

374
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:55.470
A-Are you all right?

375
00:16:55.470 --> 00:16:58.870
Yes. I drank a little too much.

376
00:16:59.290 --> 00:17:02.200
I will never sing karaoke again.

377
00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:04.290
R-Right.

378
00:17:04.840 --> 00:17:06.150
I—

379
00:17:13.520 --> 00:17:14.940
I-I'm sorry!

380
00:17:14.940 --> 00:17:16.270
Uh, it's okay.

381
00:17:16.270 --> 00:17:17.020
Bye.

382
00:17:19.020 --> 00:17:21.630
<i>Today's the worst day of my life.</i>

383
00:17:21.630 --> 00:17:24.150
<i>I want to die. Just curl up and die!</i>

384
00:17:24.550 --> 00:17:26.940
<i>Should I have made sure she got home?</i>

385
00:17:26.940 --> 00:17:31.150
<i>I could say "thank you" 
or "good night," at least.</i>

386
00:17:31.150 --> 00:17:33.230
<i>It's still not too late to do so.</i>

387
00:17:35.410 --> 00:17:40.290
<i>I could have helped her out 
by singing a duet with her back there.</i>

388
00:17:40.290 --> 00:17:42.460
<i>Why didn't I get up and join her?</i>

389
00:17:43.790 --> 00:17:46.080
<i>I'm so pathetic.</i>

390
00:17:55.050 --> 00:17:56.460
How our love started?

391
00:17:56.460 --> 00:18:02.080
Yes, the story of how we met, 
and eventually decided to marry.

392
00:18:02.080 --> 00:18:03.440
It'll be made-up, of course.

393
00:18:03.830 --> 00:18:05.570
Good point.

394
00:18:05.570 --> 00:18:08.150
We don't know what we'll be asked, or when.

395
00:18:08.150 --> 00:18:12.110
And so, please fill out this profile.

396
00:18:12.110 --> 00:18:15.250
I have tomorrow off, 
so I will go gather materials.

397
00:18:15.250 --> 00:18:16.320
Materials?

398
00:18:16.320 --> 00:18:18.680
Yes, in YHM.

399
00:18:19.520 --> 00:18:23.960
<i>With Yokohama as the setting, I'll think up 
a story for our first date and proposal.</i>

400
00:18:24.320 --> 00:18:27.210
<i>It's just like making a pamphlet for work.</i>

401
00:18:32.220 --> 00:18:34.720
<i>First, the tale of how we got together.</i>

402
00:18:34.720 --> 00:18:38.720
Marriage Project Setup Questionnaire

403
00:18:35.230 --> 00:18:38.720
Wow, Ohara-kun wrote very precise responses.

404
00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:41.720
I am 24 years old.

405
00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:41.720
<i>He's 24.</i>

406
00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:45.730
<i>Two years younger than me, 
and yet such firm character.</i>

407
00:18:45.730 --> 00:18:47.410
<i>Ohara-kun...</i>

408
00:18:50.020 --> 00:18:51.070
Zone

409
00:18:53.200 --> 00:18:57.490
<i>I tried to conjure him up 
for this imaginary date,</i>

410
00:18:57.780 --> 00:18:58.950
Zone

411
00:18:58.020 --> 00:19:02.010
<i>but of all things, I can't remember his face.</i>

412
00:19:00.030 --> 00:19:01.200
Zone

413
00:19:02.010 --> 00:19:04.500
<i>Even though we've worked across 
from each other for two years.</i>

414
00:19:02.290 --> 00:19:03.450
Zone

415
00:19:05.190 --> 00:19:08.380
<i>Is this how little interest 
I have in other people?</i>

416
00:19:08.680 --> 00:19:10.920
<i>Just how heartless am I?</i>

417
00:19:12.630 --> 00:19:16.270
<i>No matter how much 
I refine this fake project,</i>

418
00:19:16.270 --> 00:19:18.140
<i>there's no way it's going to turn out well.</i>

419
00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:21.140
<i>Ohara-kun, I'm sorry.</i>

420
00:19:21.890 --> 00:19:24.140
<i>I got you to go along with this dumb idea,</i>

421
00:19:24.820 --> 00:19:29.490
<i>and I really am sorry 
that it will crash and burn.</i>

422
00:19:35.480 --> 00:19:38.660
<i>But we can't call it off now.</i>

423
00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:41.240
<i>It's going to cause more and more trouble.</i>

424
00:19:42.070 --> 00:19:43.650
<i>What am I supposed to do?</i>

425
00:19:45.720 --> 00:19:47.670
H-Honjoji-san.

426
00:19:49.880 --> 00:19:51.770
O-Ohara-kun!

427
00:19:53.090 --> 00:19:57.640
U-Um, please let me help you 
come up with the love story!

428
00:20:07.380 --> 00:20:10.720
So, do you like Ferris wheels?

429
00:20:10.720 --> 00:20:11.400
No.

430
00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:16.030
I don't particularly like them, 
but there's something I want to do.

431
00:20:16.030 --> 00:20:18.660
I-I see.

432
00:20:20.310 --> 00:20:23.520
<i>Honjoji-san has concrete ideas about this.</i>

433
00:20:23.520 --> 00:20:25.830
<i>I shouldn't have come after all.</i>

434
00:20:26.640 --> 00:20:28.670
<i>What's that nice smell?</i>

435
00:20:29.190 --> 00:20:31.650
<i>Is it the scent of her hair?</i>

436
00:20:31.650 --> 00:20:33.800
I got a lot of materials today.

437
00:20:34.240 --> 00:20:37.170
Like the Red Brick Warehouse, 
and Landmark Tower.

438
00:20:37.170 --> 00:20:39.140
L-Looks good.

439
00:20:39.140 --> 00:20:43.520
And also, there's something I found 
and bought along the way.

440
00:20:45.480 --> 00:20:47.320
R-Rings?

441
00:20:47.320 --> 00:20:50.440
They're wedding rings, just not expensive.

442
00:20:50.980 --> 00:20:54.500
I think they'll make our 
wedding story more convincing.

443
00:20:54.940 --> 00:20:57.510
<i>I-I'm sweating now.</i>

444
00:20:57.510 --> 00:21:03.280
<i>If we put these on, it'll be like 
we're really getting married.</i>

445
00:21:04.420 --> 00:21:05.910
Go on, Ohara-kun.

446
00:21:05.910 --> 00:21:07.910
<i>She didn't hesitate at all.</i>

447
00:21:09.710 --> 00:21:12.470
<i>She went to the trouble of buying these?</i>

448
00:21:12.470 --> 00:21:15.250
And I have a favor to ask of you.

449
00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:19.070
Could you think of what 
to say for a proposal?

450
00:21:19.070 --> 00:21:20.260
Proposal?!

451
00:21:20.260 --> 00:21:21.740
That's right.

452
00:21:21.740 --> 00:21:24.590
I came up with how we got together 
and acquired some vignettes,

453
00:21:24.590 --> 00:21:28.250
but I haven't come up 
with the proposal at the end.

454
00:21:28.250 --> 00:21:33.810
My idea is that we ride a Ferris wheel, 
and when it gets to the very top,

455
00:21:33.810 --> 00:21:37.650
that's when you propose to me.

456
00:21:37.650 --> 00:21:40.510
Th-That is romantic.

457
00:21:40.510 --> 00:21:41.730
It is.

458
00:21:42.110 --> 00:21:48.370
Would you mind being the one 
to think of the words you use?

459
00:21:48.370 --> 00:21:51.760
<i>I-I know I said I wanted 
to help with the project,</i>

460
00:21:51.760 --> 00:21:53.620
<i>but suddenly, I have this important task?</i>

461
00:21:53.620 --> 00:21:55.850
I'll think of something, if you can't do it.

462
00:21:55.850 --> 00:21:59.130
Oh, I'll do it. Please allow me to.

463
00:21:59.670 --> 00:22:01.850
<i>It's too late to turn back now.</i>

464
00:22:01.850 --> 00:22:03.590
<i>I need to think of something.</i>

465
00:22:03.920 --> 00:22:07.690
<i>And I don't want to disappoint her 
by saying something boring.</i>

466
00:22:09.950 --> 00:22:13.070
<i>Uh oh, I might have stressed him out.</i>

467
00:22:13.070 --> 00:22:15.060
<i>I should have asked him to do something else.</i>

468
00:22:15.060 --> 00:22:16.400
U-Um!

469
00:22:16.400 --> 00:22:19.150
H-How about these words?

470
00:22:19.150 --> 00:22:20.400
Y-Yes?

471
00:22:24.860 --> 00:22:25.700
P—

472
00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:28.330
Please marry me.

473
00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:33.630
<i>Huh? I can't say it.</i>

474
00:22:33.630 --> 00:22:36.540
<i>It's right there in my mind, 
but it won't come out.</i>

475
00:22:36.890 --> 00:22:40.130
<i>If I say this, everything will change.</i>

476
00:22:40.130 --> 00:22:41.800
<i>That's the way it feels.</i>

477
00:22:42.290 --> 00:22:44.430
<i>These words are incredible.</i>

478
00:22:44.750 --> 00:22:47.240
<i>I've heard them in countless 
TV shows, and yet...</i>

479
00:22:50.350 --> 00:22:51.560
I'm sorry.

480
00:22:51.560 --> 00:22:53.820
I still haven't thought of anything.

481
00:22:54.970 --> 00:22:56.060
Sorry.

482
00:22:56.690 --> 00:22:58.850
I <i>will</i> think of something later.

483
00:22:58.850 --> 00:23:01.070
Uh, hey, it's okay.

484
00:23:01.070 --> 00:23:02.640
It's all okay.

485
00:23:07.280 --> 00:23:10.460
Ohara-kun, the view is beautiful.

486
00:23:12.060 --> 00:23:15.990
Today, I did lots of things 
I don't usually do.

487
00:23:16.510 --> 00:23:20.450
It was like an ordinary life.

488
00:23:22.260 --> 00:23:27.090
Ohara-kun, please take your time 
thinking of a proposal.

489
00:23:27.500 --> 00:23:30.970
I'll wait as long as it takes.

